<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-08-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="105" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d105">
                    <head>No. 105.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Hosmer</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-08-27"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 27,
                            1887</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>The Government of Mexico assures the Government of the United States that it
                        will not interfere with Guatemala’s domestic affairs and the United States
                        rely on this assurance.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>